description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Advert: Research Nurse Band 5 1.0 WTE post based at Peterborough City Hospital.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you motivated, resourceful, curious? Can you contribute to and embrace change? Are you looking to join a dynamic research team? North West Anglia NHS Foundation trust is one of the fastest growing research centres in the East of England. We are looking for a Research Nurse to join us. You must be highly organised with excellent interpersonal and IT skills and a “can do” approach. You will be required to work effectively within our clinical research team across the Trust. Attention to detail and the ability to work to deadlines are essential. Research nursing is a stimulating and rewarding career pathway that this Trust can support and develop.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will join a team responsible for the delivery of research across a range of specialties as required including medicine and surgery. This role gives an opportunity for the post holder to grow their knowledge and skills in a variety of clinical research settings. You will work with R&amp;D Office staff, local clinicians, specialist nurses, different specialty research teams and relevant research networks, primarily concentrating on the delivery of research studies.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will assist with participant identification and recruitment, obtaining informed consent from patients and will have responsibility for organising patient visits, delivery of the interventions, completing case report forms and maintenance of study documentation according to Good Clinical Practice (ICH -GCP).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience working in a clinical research environment is not essential but a motivation to develop this career pathway and experience in a relevant clinical setting is essential. A full research training and mentoring programme is in place.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role will offer the right candidate a fantastic opportunity to contribute to the team at one of the country’s newest and most developing research Trusts. Please contact Senior Research Nurse Torby Christenssen by email at victoria.christenssen@nhs.net in the first instance leaving and contact number and best time to call if you require an informal chat.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Previous applicants need not apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name Torby Christenssen Job title Senior Research Nurse Email address victoria.christenssen@nhs.net Telephone number 01480 363536&lt;/p&gt;
